rComments: She has high standards for her students.  She taught me to be precise in my translations.  A brilliant Indologist with an eye for detail.  A fascinating lady to chat with.  In class she can often get off topic and talk about Hindutva or give long personal anecdotes.

S. Sandahl is a great proff. She has extensive knowledge on South Asia and has put together a serious academic seminar on the Partition of British India. If your genuinely interested in the subject matter, you will do well. She is a fair marker; however, this is not a "bird course." Nor will this course satisfy any exoticized notions of South Asia.
She is tough on her students, but it all pays off when you realize how much you have learned from all that hard work she made you do. She is a fascinating person to talk to as well.
